
BitLocker can be configured or used to
  • encrypts the Windows OS drive
  • lock → Windows/booting[startup process] until the user provides a PIN (personal identification number) or inserts a removable drive (for example → hardware/USB) with the startup key


The level of protection provided by BitLocker can be increased with a → hardware/security/TPM[TPM] version 1.2 or higher. Without such a module,
BitLocker can be used, but the user has insert a → hardware/USB after hibernation.

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/manage-bde_exe[`manage-bde.exe`]

  → Windows/security
